Application Deployment and Description  To deploy the application, I used Streamlit, a Python-based framework designed for rapid development of interactive data science and machine learning applications. Streamlit allows users to input data through a web interface and obtain real-time predictions along with explanations.

A comprehensive machine learning system for predicting and preventing player churn in gaming applications. This end-to-end solution includes data pipelines, ML models, real-time APIs, interactive dashboards, and A/B testing frameworks.

Ununennium (Element 119, the next alkali metal) represents the cutting edge of satellite imagery machine learning. This library provides a unified, GPU-first framework for end-to-end Earth observation workflows, from cloud-native data access through model training to deployment.

This project presents an adaptive hybrid quantumclassical machine learning framework for drug discovery that dynamically invokes quantum circuits based on prediction uncertainty. By selectively applying shallow or deep quantum computation only when needed, the system reduces quantum resource usage while enabling efficient decision-making.
A computer vision and machine learning pipeline on a distributed framework. Designed for an embedded network on low voltage IoT hardware.

RECLAIM (Reservoir Estimation of Capacity Loss using AI-based Methods) is a globally scalable machine learning framework to predict absolute sedimentation rates using observed records and multi-decadal Earth observations from satellite data.

This project develops predictive machine learning models to guide ecosystem restoration efforts in Delhi by analyzing air quality, water quality, vegetation, biodiversity, and socio-economic data. Based on IPCC AR6 framework and utilizing open government data from data.gov.in.

AI-based real-time insider threat detection system that analyzes network traffic and user behavior using machine learning models. The framework integrates multiple data sources, generates severity scores, and triggers automated email alerts for proactive cybersecurity response.

Mapping Alternate Scenarios of Forest Intactness (MASFI) is a cloud-based machine learning framework. It uses XGBoost regression and remote sensing data such as GEDI LiDAR to create high-resolution maps and statistics, supporting protected area planning and management.

A data-driven approach to discovering inorganic perovskite gas sensing materials using machine learning and first-principles descriptors. The framework predicts adsorption energy, gassurface interactions and sensing performance toward NH, NO, NO, HS, and SO to enable efficient and selective gas sensor design.

SIGMA (Smart Intelligent Grid Management Architecture) .SIGMA is an AI framework designed to bring intelligence, resilience, and automation to modern power grids. The system automates essential data cleaning operations, including missing value handling, outlier capping, duplicate removal, feature encoding, and scaling to prepare data for machine learning tasks.

VeriCredit is an enterprise-grade AI governance framework designed to evaluate, validate, and audit AI-generated credit decision explanations produced by Large Language Models (LLMs). The system ensures that credit explanations are faithful to underlying machine learning models, free from bias, legally compliant, and stable across prompts.

FlaMMA (Flaky Mitigation & Monitoring Approach) is a framework for detecting, mitigating, and monitoring flaky tests in real projects. It combines rerun analysis, machine learning, and automated repair strategies to improve test reliability, reduce CI instability, and support more trustworthy software testing.

The project combines macro-finance theory, econometric modeling, and modern machine learning methods to build a structural interpretation of liquidity-driven markets.
